Definition: somewhat ill or prone to illness
Example: my poor ailing grandmother; feeling a bit indisposed today; you look a little peaked; feeling poorly; a sickly child; is unwell and can't come to work
Synonyms: indisposed, peaked, p, poorly, sickly, unwell, noun, state, unwellness, under_the_weather, seedy, somewhat, ill, or, prone, to, illness, my, poor, grandmother, feeling, a, bit, today, you, look, little, child, is, and, can, t, come, work
Category: adj.all
